David Keatts commented on [medium] Advanced filters may be wonky. Someone on the BSB Discord mentioned it, and I went and picked Sigarda, and tried to filter decks running Swords to Plowshares, and the number of decks went up somehow: "the first debugging hint was that the url had ?f=undefined:<cardname> rather than ?f:in=<cardname>.  figuring out why this was happening was tough because I wrote the advanced filters code in what, 2015? (jesus)

turns out, the new typeahead (which I updated for the searchbar) has a slightly different html structure, and the javascript was looking in the wrong place for the "with/without" dropdown.  instead of calling this.parent().parent(), now it's this.parent().parent().parent()."
attachments.text:
